n contends. He argues against Halevi’s triumphalism and in favor of using the Sinai covenant for evaluating the religious significance of Israel, for this approach gives meaning to Zionists’ religious commitments while also empowering secular Israelis to reengage with the Jewish tradition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJewsxIdentityxIsrael. 0aJewszIsraelxIdentity. 0aJudaismxIsrael. 0aJudaismzIsrael. 0aSecularismxIsrael. 0aSecularismzIsrael. 0aZionismxPhilosophy. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013051540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300130515423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300130515/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles